					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>A pillar set up in front of the same temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">No king: Prabhava: c. 13th century.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged much. It refers to a certain <hi rend="italic">Mahāpradhāna</hi> Śiṅgaya-daṇṇāyaka and to another Daṇṇāyaka (name not clear) <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Valadēvar. It records the gift probably by the above-mentioned Daṇṇāyaka of a <hi rend="italic">nandā</hi> lamp to be burnt from the month of Kārttigai in the above-mentioned cyclic year in the temple of Āṉaikāttaperumāḷ in Śrī-Mādhavachchaturvēdi maṅgalam.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
